.TH "gpiod_configure_flags" 9 "gpiod_configure_flags" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gpiod_configure_flags \- helper function to configure a given GPIO
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gpiod_configure_flags
.BI "(struct gpio_desc *desc "  ","
.BI "const char *con_id "  ","
.BI "unsigned long lflags "  ","
.BI "enum gpiod_flags dflags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "desc" 12
gpio whose value will be assigned
.IP "con_id" 12
function within the GPIO consumer
.IP "lflags" 12
bitmask of gpio_lookup_flags GPIO_* values - returned from
\fBof_find_gpio\fP or \fBof_get_gpio_hog\fP
.IP "dflags" 12
gpiod_flags - optional GPIO initialization flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return 0 on success, -ENOENT if no GPIO has been assigned to the
requested function and/or index, or another \fBIS_ERR\fP code if an error
occurred while trying to acquire the GPIO.
